9
00:00:55,030 --> 00:00:57,410
You're Mr. Yoon Jeong Jae, right?

10
00:01:07,590 --> 00:01:09,670
Do you remember me?

11
00:01:16,240 --> 00:01:19,730
P-Please give me a minute.

12
00:01:20,970 --> 00:01:22,200
I'll call Hae Joon–

13
00:01:22,200 --> 00:01:26,540
I hope to keep it a secret from Hae Joon that I'm here.

14
00:01:26,540 --> 00:01:28,050
Sorry?

15
00:01:32,110 --> 00:01:33,940
Have a seat.

16
00:01:44,580 --> 00:01:46,730
Let's talk, just the two of us.

17
00:01:57,650 --> 00:02:02,400
   

18
00:02:06,260 --> 00:02:08,520
   

19
00:02:08,520 --> 00:02:11,190
   

20
00:02:31,960 --> 00:02:34,860
Don't you remember lending me money?

21
00:02:34,860 --> 00:02:37,290
I remember lending it to you,

22
00:02:37,290 --> 00:02:40,120
and I remember the exact amount.

23
00:02:40,120 --> 00:02:44,250
But this is too much.

24
00:02:45,210 --> 00:02:47,300
I put some more in there.

25
00:02:47,300 --> 00:02:49,610
Why did you put more?

26
00:02:49,610 --> 00:02:53,180
It must've cost a lot to raise Hae Joon.

27
00:02:53,180 --> 00:02:55,840
It'll cost more for college.

28
00:03:03,740 --> 00:03:06,490
Thank you for the coffee.

29
00:03:06,490 --> 00:03:08,810
You're leaving?

30
00:03:08,810 --> 00:03:11,350
This is so sudden...

31
00:03:11,350 --> 00:03:13,440
Pardon...

32
00:03:13,440 --> 00:03:15,770
Pardon me!

33
00:03:15,770 --> 00:03:18,530
Wait a minute!

34
00:03:19,330 --> 00:03:23,870
You came all the way here. Why won't you see Hae Joon?

35
00:03:23,870 --> 00:03:25,840
What would be the point?

36
00:03:25,840 --> 00:03:28,280
What do you mean? Well, of course...

37
00:03:29,900 --> 00:03:33,870
It'd be nice to see him, even for a moment.

38
00:03:33,870 --> 00:03:37,070
Why see him when I'm not here to take him with me?

39
00:03:39,690 --> 00:03:43,650
Is it hard to tell him his mom paid her debt and left?

40
00:03:43,650 --> 00:03:46,700
Just tell him it's great he doesn't have to pay you back.

41
00:03:46,700 --> 00:03:50,510
That's not the issue. Your child would want to see you!

42
00:03:51,190 --> 00:03:53,950
Do you know how long he waited for you?

43
00:03:53,950 --> 00:03:56,940
How can I tell him you just came and left?

44
00:03:56,940 --> 00:03:59,430
Don't be like this and–

45
00:04:05,320 --> 00:04:07,320
Yes, fine.

46
00:04:07,320 --> 00:04:13,220
If you insist, I'll accept only the money I lent you.

47
00:04:14,030 --> 00:04:16,360
This leaves no resentment, right?

48
00:04:16,360 --> 00:04:18,300
Take care.

49
00:04:18,950 --> 00:04:20,840
Mr. Yoon Jeong Jae.

50
00:04:22,170 --> 00:04:24,500
Why did you lend me money?

51
00:04:25,450 --> 00:04:26,970
Excuse me?

52
00:04:27,870 --> 00:04:31,650
No matter how I think about it, we were almost strangers.

53
00:04:31,650 --> 00:04:34,400
You lent it too easily.

54
00:04:36,670 --> 00:04:38,880
It wasn't easy for me,

55
00:04:38,880 --> 00:04:43,790
and you must've had your reasons for asking when we were essentially strangers.

56
00:04:46,280 --> 00:04:48,650
You seem to understand everyone's circumstances.

57
00:04:48,650 --> 00:04:52,210
Yes, it's not that hard once you try to understand.

58
00:04:55,080 --> 00:04:57,000
Just take it.

59
00:04:57,920 --> 00:04:59,850
Wait, Ms. Seo Hyeon...

60
00:05:02,710 --> 00:05:06,910
What am I supposed to tell him?

61
00:05:08,100 --> 00:05:10,710
It's melting! Let's run!

62
00:05:10,710 --> 00:05:12,650
H-Hey! Time out!

63
00:05:12,650 --> 00:05:15,010
- Time out! 
 - Gosh.

64
00:05:24,280 --> 00:05:25,970
- What? 
 - Pardon?

65
00:05:26,820 --> 00:05:29,400
- Nothing. Let's go. 
 - Okay.

66
00:05:45,320 --> 00:05:48,380
   

67
00:06:07,460 --> 00:06:09,810
   

68
00:06:36,760 --> 00:06:39,500
He never sleeps at night.

69
00:06:39,500 --> 00:06:42,580
At least let him sleep during the day.

70
00:06:55,290 --> 00:06:56,670
   

71
00:06:56,670 --> 00:06:59,100
This has been ringing for a while.

72
00:07:03,820 --> 00:07:06,130
   

73
00:07:10,720 --> 00:07:11,910
Hello?

74
00:07:11,910 --> 00:07:13,900
 Put So Hui on the phone. 

75
00:07:14,830 --> 00:07:16,940
Why are you asking me for So Hui?

76
00:07:16,940 --> 00:07:20,580
 She told Ahjumma she was going to the restaurant to see you. 

77
00:07:20,580 --> 00:07:22,590
So Hui's gone?

78
00:07:24,130 --> 00:07:25,770
Since when?

79
00:07:38,030 --> 00:07:40,250
Welcome!

80
00:07:41,900 --> 00:07:45,040
Ahjusshi, did So Hui come here?

81
00:07:45,040 --> 00:07:47,630
- So Hui? 
 - Did So Hui not come?

82
00:07:47,630 --> 00:07:49,770
Why? Is she gone?

83
00:07:49,770 --> 00:07:51,900
Yes, I think she left by herself.

84
00:07:51,900 --> 00:07:53,840
She didn't come to the restaurant.

85
00:07:54,590 --> 00:07:57,560
You shouldn't be asking me that!

86
00:07:59,310 --> 00:08:02,470
She might be on her way here. Please let me know if she comes.

87
00:08:02,470 --> 00:08:04,110
Yes, all right. I'll do that.

88
00:08:04,110 --> 00:08:06,430
I'll search nearby.

89
00:08:26,170 --> 00:08:28,100
   

90
00:08:35,860 --> 00:08:37,930
So Hui!

91
00:08:41,640 --> 00:08:43,980
 Aigoo, goodbye! Take care. 

92
00:08:43,980 --> 00:08:47,770
 Take care! Goodbye! 
   

93
00:08:52,010 --> 00:08:56,720
If you wait a moment, the police will help find your mom.

94
00:08:56,720 --> 00:09:00,670
I'm not looking for my mom. I'm looking for my oppa.

95
00:09:02,600 --> 00:09:04,240
Over here! Over here!

96
00:09:04,240 --> 00:09:07,540
Hello, we are from the Gangpyeong Police Station.

97
00:09:07,540 --> 00:09:09,320
Is that her?

98
00:09:13,350 --> 00:09:16,590
What's your name, Little Girl?

99
00:09:16,590 --> 00:09:19,060
Where are your mom and dad?

100
00:09:20,370 --> 00:09:22,980
She rode the taxi here by herself around 2:00 p.m.?

101
00:09:22,980 --> 00:09:26,940
That's right. She said she came looking for her mom.

102
00:09:26,940 --> 00:09:28,950
Where did she get in the taxi?

103
00:09:28,950 --> 00:09:31,340
She didn't say.

104
00:09:37,240 --> 00:09:41,500
Was there a report of a missing child?

105
00:09:52,790 --> 00:09:55,070
Please hold.

106
00:09:55,070 --> 00:09:56,330
   

107
00:09:59,800 --> 00:10:01,370
When?

108
00:10:03,050 --> 00:10:05,010
Off to the restaurant by herself?

109
00:10:18,240 --> 00:10:19,930
Are you So Hui?

110
00:10:19,930 --> 00:10:22,550
   

111
00:10:37,990 --> 00:10:40,040
Oppa!

112
00:10:40,620 --> 00:10:42,050
Where did you find her?

113
00:10:42,050 --> 00:10:43,830
At a noodle shop in the next town.

114
00:10:43,830 --> 00:10:47,520
I responded to a call and found her there.

115
00:10:48,250 --> 00:10:50,250
How could you come here alone?

116
00:10:50,250 --> 00:10:53,320
Thank goodness we found her, so all is good.

117
00:10:53,320 --> 00:10:55,960
What if she does this again?

118
00:10:55,960 --> 00:10:58,950
Do you think we will be lucky to find you again?

119
00:11:01,840 --> 00:11:05,640
Oppa was just really worried about you, So Hui.

120
00:11:05,640 --> 00:11:07,630
Really?

121
00:11:14,250 --> 00:11:16,470
Jeong So Hui!

122
00:11:22,080 --> 00:11:24,590
Who said you could leave home by yourself?

123
00:11:24,590 --> 00:11:27,000
Do you know how worried I was?

124
00:11:28,820 --> 00:11:30,450
Let's go.

125
00:11:32,980 --> 00:11:34,990
Oppa.

126
00:11:35,540 --> 00:11:37,220
Let's go!

127
00:11:41,960 --> 00:11:44,510
You won't even greet me now?

128
00:11:44,510 --> 00:11:47,970
Haven't you children learned you should greet your elders?

129
00:11:47,970 --> 00:11:49,410
I did–

130
00:11:49,410 --> 00:11:51,210
They did.

131
00:11:51,210 --> 00:11:53,010
You're the one who didn't see because you ignored them.

132
00:11:53,010 --> 00:11:56,350
They roamed for over an hour looking for So Hui.

133
00:11:57,760 --> 00:12:01,710
So Hui has never left home by herself like this before.

134
00:12:01,710 --> 00:12:03,210
You're the only oppa she has.

135
00:12:03,210 --> 00:12:05,510
This wouldn't happen if you visited your sister first!

136
00:12:05,510 --> 00:12:08,730
How is this San Ha's fault? What were you doing?

137
00:12:08,730 --> 00:12:10,860
Do you expect me to monitor her continuously?

138
00:12:10,860 --> 00:12:14,510
It hasn't been long since San Ha and the child first met.

139
00:12:14,510 --> 00:12:17,000
They're not close enough for sudden visits.

140
00:12:17,000 --> 00:12:20,330
Time is irrelevant. They're family!

141
00:12:23,740 --> 00:12:27,230
Do you know how glad I was to see you after ten years?

142
00:12:27,230 --> 00:12:29,520
"My son has grown so much since I last saw him."

143
00:12:29,520 --> 00:12:31,810
"So Hui would love to live with her oppa."

144
00:12:31,810 --> 00:12:33,980
"Fine, I should try."

145
00:12:33,980 --> 00:12:36,660
"I should try to forgive you."

146
00:12:39,590 --> 00:12:42,100
I said I don't need your forgiveness.

147
00:12:42,100 --> 00:12:45,800
You never contacted me when you got remarried or had So Hui. Why now, suddenly?

148
00:12:45,800 --> 00:12:49,500
- That's why I'm doing this at least now– 
 - That's why!

149
00:12:51,060 --> 00:12:52,740
Please...

150
00:12:52,740 --> 00:12:55,530
Please stop trying.

151
00:12:57,390 --> 00:12:59,650
How could you...

152
00:12:59,650 --> 00:13:04,160
Shouldn't I be the one saying such words?

153
00:13:04,160 --> 00:13:07,710
Shouldn't you have begged for forgiveness before I tried to forgive you?

154
00:13:07,710 --> 00:13:08,980
Whose fault is this?

155
00:13:08,980 --> 00:13:11,640
- Please stop! 
 - Why should I stop?

156
00:13:11,640 --> 00:13:14,460
Why are you yelling at me when it was your fault?

157
00:13:14,460 --> 00:13:16,040
It was your fault.

158
00:13:16,040 --> 00:13:17,500
- It was all your fault! 
 - Stop!

159
00:13:17,500 --> 00:13:20,800
- She died because of you! 
 - Enough!

160
00:13:23,400 --> 00:13:24,750
Come out.

161
00:13:24,750 --> 00:13:26,670
Come out!

162
00:13:59,770 --> 00:14:02,280
It's okay. Don't cry.

163
00:14:02,280 --> 00:14:03,970
It's okay.

164
00:14:15,920 --> 00:14:18,130
Where are you going?

165
00:14:19,820 --> 00:14:22,180
Wait for us.

166
00:14:25,740 --> 00:14:28,380
Give him some time to resolve his thoughts.

167
00:14:28,380 --> 00:14:30,560
He didn't look back once.

168
00:14:30,560 --> 00:14:32,910
He doesn't want to show us his face.

169
00:14:43,690 --> 00:14:46,710
Where are you taking me?

170
00:14:48,030 --> 00:14:49,710
That's right.

171
00:14:51,460 --> 00:14:55,800
Before you left ten years ago, I blamed you.

172
00:14:55,800 --> 00:14:57,590
I thought it was all your fault.

173
00:14:57,590 --> 00:14:59,090
What are you saying?

174
00:14:59,090 --> 00:15:01,280
You're a weak person.

175
00:15:01,280 --> 00:15:05,650
I'm well aware you're not strong enough to admit your mistakes,

176
00:15:05,650 --> 00:15:10,650
so I didn't want to remind you that it was your fault.

177
00:15:10,650 --> 00:15:11,840
What are you talking about?

178
00:15:11,840 --> 00:15:14,910
You're not the one who should be doing the forgiving!

179
00:15:19,680 --> 00:15:22,580
I even gave you a divorce so you hurt less.

180
00:15:23,430 --> 00:15:26,410
I did everything you wanted.

181
00:15:26,410 --> 00:15:28,800
You "gave me a divorce"?

182
00:15:28,800 --> 00:15:30,460
Jeong Hui.

183
00:15:31,820 --> 00:15:34,400
I loved you that much.

184
00:15:35,200 --> 00:15:38,020
How about me? Do you think I didn't?

185
00:15:38,020 --> 00:15:40,680
Do you think I was a cold-blooded person?

186
00:15:40,680 --> 00:15:42,160
Did I go crazy?

187
00:15:42,160 --> 00:15:46,340
Why do you think I married a lowly civil servant with nothing to his name?

188
00:15:46,340 --> 00:15:48,490
What? "Love"?

189
00:15:48,490 --> 00:15:52,150
When I said I was depressed after spending my youth having two children,

190
00:15:52,150 --> 00:15:54,680
did you even pretend to hear me?

191
00:15:54,680 --> 00:15:57,370
You obsessed over your work performance!

192
00:15:57,370 --> 00:15:59,500
What did you say when you finally came home?

193
00:15:59,500 --> 00:16:02,500
"I think I'll be able to catch him. I just need a little more time."

194
00:16:02,500 --> 00:16:06,090
You didn't care how lonely and miserable I was.

195
00:16:06,990 --> 00:16:08,400
You're right.

196
00:16:08,400 --> 00:16:11,470
- Everything you said is true, but– 
 - That day,

197
00:16:11,470 --> 00:16:13,970
you weren't home either.

198
00:16:13,970 --> 00:16:16,400
Was I the only one not at home?

199
00:16:16,400 --> 00:16:19,030
Were you the only one free to go after criminals?

200
00:16:19,030 --> 00:16:23,020
How are you the only one who is always righteous and dignified?

201
00:16:24,420 --> 00:16:25,800
Right.

202
00:16:26,800 --> 00:16:29,370
After my child died,

203
00:16:29,370 --> 00:16:33,030
forget justice and dignity. Nothing mattered anymore!

204
00:16:33,030 --> 00:16:35,160
But what about San Ha?

205
00:16:35,160 --> 00:16:37,320
Is San Ha not our child?

206
00:16:37,320 --> 00:16:40,400
Don't you feel sorry for him?

207
00:16:40,400 --> 00:16:46,370
That little boy watched his younger sister suffocate to death!

208
00:16:46,370 --> 00:16:50,870
 Have you ever thought about the emotional state he has been in? 

209
00:16:51,540 --> 00:16:53,720
 He was alone with So Jeong. 

210
00:16:53,720 --> 00:16:55,640
 What was he doing then? 

211
00:16:55,640 --> 00:16:57,820
 Didn't you ever think about that? 

212
00:16:57,820 --> 00:17:00,360
 Have you never thought that before? 

213
00:17:01,490 --> 00:17:03,270
 To forgive you. 

214
00:17:03,270 --> 00:17:04,880
 I'm going to try to forgive you. 

215
00:17:04,880 --> 00:17:07,900
 Shouldn't you have begged for forgiveness before I tried to forgive you? 

216
00:17:07,900 --> 00:17:09,800
 It was your fault. It was all your fault! 

217
00:17:09,800 --> 00:17:12,080
 She died because of you! 

218
00:17:18,510 --> 00:17:20,210
   

219
00:17:20,210 --> 00:17:23,150
 How about an adult? Is there an adult with you? 

220
00:17:23,150 --> 00:17:26,940
 No one's here. No one... 

221
00:17:57,210 --> 00:17:59,940
   

222
00:18:28,410 --> 00:18:30,000
 When Ahjumma left this place, 

223
00:18:30,000 --> 00:18:32,740
do you know how cold she was to Kim San Ha?

224
00:18:32,740 --> 00:18:34,880
She told me to "keep him," as if he were some object.

225
00:18:34,880 --> 00:18:36,700
She never once held his hand.

226
00:18:36,700 --> 00:18:40,120
And now, she wants to "forgive him"?

227
00:18:43,750 --> 00:18:46,880
Why are you silent? Am I wrong?

228
00:18:53,040 --> 00:18:54,460
Not too long ago...

229
00:18:54,460 --> 00:18:58,500
 In this world, toxic families also exist. 

230
00:18:58,500 --> 00:19:01,100
 My mom and I are like that. 

231
00:19:02,270 --> 00:19:06,880
At the time, I couldn't understand how he could say something so harsh.

232
00:19:06,880 --> 00:19:08,550
But I think I can understand now.

233
00:19:08,550 --> 00:19:11,050
I've told you all this time how scary Ahjumma is!

234
00:19:11,050 --> 00:19:13,410
How was I supposed to know with just that?

235
00:19:13,410 --> 00:19:15,500
I can only understand if I know more.

236
00:19:15,500 --> 00:19:17,770
He sneaks into his room at the mention of his mom.

237
00:19:17,770 --> 00:19:20,950
It's because he's trying to hold back.

238
00:20:06,910 --> 00:20:07,940
 Why? 

239
00:20:07,940 --> 00:20:09,980
When? At what time?

240
00:20:09,980 --> 00:20:12,000
Did he not even eat breakfast?

241
00:20:13,220 --> 00:20:17,150
Aigoo, Joo Won is the only one who cares about San Ha.

242
00:20:17,150 --> 00:20:19,570
Ahjusshi.

243
00:20:19,570 --> 00:20:23,040
I told Ahjumma not to contact San Ha for the time being.

244
00:20:23,040 --> 00:20:27,500
His grandmother is in Japan with his uncle, so he'll hear less from her, too.

245
00:20:27,500 --> 00:20:29,820
Don't worry about it.

246
00:20:29,820 --> 00:20:31,550
"For the time being"?

247
00:20:31,550 --> 00:20:34,710
From when to when specifically?

248
00:20:35,930 --> 00:20:39,630
Well... The soup tastes great.

249
00:20:40,560 --> 00:20:42,820
You're not sure, are you?

250
00:20:44,770 --> 00:20:47,840
He probably couldn't sleep before going to school.

251
00:20:47,840 --> 00:20:51,490
Dad, don't you have anything better than jujube tea?

252
00:20:51,490 --> 00:20:55,860
Something like king jujube tea or emperor jujube tea?

253
00:20:55,860 --> 00:20:58,140
I'll check in the marketplace.

254
00:20:58,140 --> 00:21:00,460
You both finish your breakfast before going.

255
00:21:00,460 --> 00:21:03,500
I'll pack you some cherry tomatoes and apples.

256
00:21:03,500 --> 00:21:05,190
Take them to San Ha later.

257
00:21:05,190 --> 00:21:08,330
Will cherry tomatoes be enough?

258
00:21:08,330 --> 00:21:10,580
Wait, why won't he eat breakfast?

259
00:21:10,580 --> 00:21:13,460
You ought to eat, no matter what,

260
00:21:13,460 --> 00:21:16,260
or you'll suffer all day at school.

261
00:21:30,960 --> 00:21:33,900
Don't wake him up. Let's just go to the snack bar.

262
00:21:55,830 --> 00:21:58,120
Did Oppa leave already?

263
00:21:59,150 --> 00:22:02,260
- I don't know. 
 - He said he was going to the library.

264
00:22:04,720 --> 00:22:06,570
Did he?

265
00:22:09,920 --> 00:22:13,370
- Hey, move aside! 
 - Let's go!

266
00:23:10,070 --> 00:23:12,840
We all ate our dinner.

267
00:23:13,500 --> 00:23:15,060
Okay.

268
00:23:16,120 --> 00:23:17,770
How much longer will you keep this up?

269
00:23:17,770 --> 00:23:19,910
Isn't this enough?

270
00:23:23,700 --> 00:23:28,600
As you said, we might just be motherless children in other people's eyes,

271
