375
00:34:06,130 --> 00:34:07,890
So Jeong.

376
00:34:14,690 --> 00:34:18,010
I was just saying I do. Just saying.

377
00:34:20,420 --> 00:34:22,570
I miss my mom, too.

378
00:34:23,380 --> 00:34:26,820
You don't know what your mom looks like, though.

379
00:34:26,820 --> 00:34:30,710
I saw her pictures, but also want to see her in person.

380
00:34:31,720 --> 00:34:33,530
You never said anything like that.

381
00:34:33,530 --> 00:34:39,270
Because if I say I miss her, my dad will be sad.

382
00:34:40,550 --> 00:34:43,800
Do you think my dad misses So Jeong, too?

383
00:34:43,800 --> 00:34:46,380
Does he have to point it out for you?

384
00:34:47,030 --> 00:34:50,180
Right? It's a given.

385
00:34:53,840 --> 00:34:56,040
I miss my mom, too.

386
00:35:00,420 --> 00:35:02,900
Of course, I do.

387
00:35:02,900 --> 00:35:08,380
19-year-old Kang Hae Joon still misses his mother.

388
00:35:08,380 --> 00:35:12,000
Why do you always pick on me? Why?

389
00:35:12,000 --> 00:35:16,830
- Whenever he thinks of his mother, Hae Joon gets teary. 
 - I said stop! Stop!

390
00:35:16,830 --> 00:35:18,600
Do you understand Korean–

391
00:35:40,160 --> 00:35:42,250
 Dad! 

