If she concentrates on it during the break,

537
00:47:17,070 --> 00:47:19,790
she'll improve drastically compared to other subjects.

538
00:47:19,790 --> 00:47:21,280
You shouldn't worry.

539
00:47:21,280 --> 00:47:23,030
Really?

540
00:47:24,780 --> 00:47:27,810
But that's only for smart children like you.

541
00:47:27,810 --> 00:47:30,910
Our Dal has to work hard. I'm not sure if she can handle it.

542
00:47:30,910 --> 00:47:34,460
Gosh, she just works hard without any strategy.

543
00:47:34,460 --> 00:47:36,830
Eat. Eat up.

544
00:47:48,470 --> 00:47:51,150
Why are you here and not eating with them?

545
00:47:53,160 --> 00:47:54,790
Well...

546
00:47:56,080 --> 00:48:01,110
Mom, I know I can't even choose from the menu

547
00:48:01,110 --> 00:48:03,850
and I messed up on math,

548
00:48:04,750 --> 00:48:09,280
but I wish you wouldn't treat me like I'm stupid in front of my peers.

549
00:48:09,280 --> 00:48:13,760
It's fine when it's just the two of us at home–

550
00:48:14,730 --> 00:48:17,700
Then, should I say my daughter is a distinguished person?

551
00:48:17,700 --> 00:48:20,580
People get annoyed when smart people are praised.

552
00:48:20,580 --> 00:48:23,370
That's just how people sympathize.

553
00:48:23,370 --> 00:48:26,910
People are more likely to help if you seem to lack a little.

554
00:48:26,910 --> 00:48:28,460
You need his notes.

555
00:48:28,460 --> 00:48:31,820
I don't need his notes.

556
00:48:31,820 --> 00:48:35,430
I'm not saying I want to act like I'm extraordinary.

557
00:48:37,020 --> 00:48:41,050
I just don't want to look like a fool in front of my friends.

558
00:48:41,050 --> 00:48:43,080
Why are you crying?

559
00:48:43,080 --> 00:48:45,540
What did I say to make you cry?

560
00:48:45,540 --> 00:48:48,760
I look so stupid.

561
00:48:59,080 --> 00:49:00,620
I think she cried.

562
00:49:00,620 --> 00:49:02,070
- She cried. 
 - Smile.

563
00:49:02,070 --> 00:49:04,420
- I can't smile. 
 - Me, either.

564
00:49:04,420 --> 00:49:07,720
Then should we tell Dal to her face that her mom is too much?

565
00:49:35,760 --> 00:49:38,930
- Farewell. 
 - Thank you for the food.

566
00:49:50,130 --> 00:49:51,880
- What? 
 - Goodness!

567
00:49:51,880 --> 00:49:54,270
Do you have a bad relationship with your mom?

568
00:49:56,650 --> 00:49:58,440
Ignore him.

569
00:49:59,540 --> 00:50:02,240
Our relationship is fine.

570
00:50:03,140 --> 00:50:04,590
Let's go to the beach!

571
00:50:04,590 --> 00:50:06,770
We just have to walk a little.

572
00:50:06,770 --> 00:50:08,280
Let's go.

573
00:50:15,590 --> 00:50:17,450
Be careful!

574
00:50:49,950 --> 00:50:51,450
Is this all you really need? 
    

575
00:50:51,450 --> 00:50:53,290
Thank you.

576
00:50:53,290 --> 00:50:54,700
It is.

577
00:50:54,700 --> 00:50:59,360
I'll show it to my mom and return it right away.

578
00:50:59,360 --> 00:51:01,550
You should join them, too.

579
00:51:01,550 --> 00:51:04,610
We came here to make you feel better.

580
00:51:04,610 --> 00:51:07,360
I feel fine, though.

581
00:51:12,280 --> 00:51:18,170
She was just acting like that in front of you guys.

582
00:51:18,170 --> 00:51:21,060
She's not like that when we are alone.

583
00:51:21,060 --> 00:51:25,650
And she's not exactly wrong.

584
00:51:27,800 --> 00:51:31,770
Do you remember how you and Joo Won became friends?

585
00:51:32,770 --> 00:51:38,180
Probably when I called Sunbae Hae Joon over when she got dragged to the incinerating facility.

586
00:51:38,180 --> 00:51:44,470
Joo Won told me you ran without even realizing your shoe had fallen off.

587
00:51:44,470 --> 00:51:46,200
That's right.

588
00:51:47,540 --> 00:51:51,900
Lawyers aren't people who simply speak well.

589
00:51:51,900 --> 00:51:56,440
Shouldn't they be like you, who spends time taking care of

590
00:51:56,440 --> 00:51:58,760
others' business like it's your own?

591
00:52:03,510 --> 00:52:07,440
Your mom's words weren't all true.

592
00:52:07,440 --> 00:52:12,170
Just think of your mom as human, too.

593
00:52:12,950 --> 00:52:15,300
Then you'll feel more at peace.

594
00:52:16,450 --> 00:52:18,370
That's what I do.

595
00:52:25,640 --> 00:52:27,970
Hey, look at this! Seaweed!

596
00:52:27,970 --> 00:52:29,890
Do they grow it here?

597
00:52:35,800 --> 00:52:37,470
Why are you laughing?

598
00:52:38,950 --> 00:52:40,830
You know I'm astute, right?

599
00:52:40,830 --> 00:52:42,530
Your friend likes Kim San Ha.

600
00:52:42,530 --> 00:52:45,240
I'm positive! They look good together.

601
00:52:47,280 --> 00:52:48,660
What the heck?

602
00:52:48,660 --> 00:52:50,530
Something came over me.

603
00:52:56,260 --> 00:52:58,240
It's Auntie!

604
00:52:58,240 --> 00:53:00,070
Okay, okay!

605
00:53:01,120 --> 00:53:02,960
- Auntie called. She said I could visit. 
 - O-Okay.

606
00:53:02,960 --> 00:53:04,930
I'm off!

607
00:53:04,930 --> 00:53:06,100
Hey!

608
00:53:06,100 --> 00:53:07,070
   

609
00:53:07,070 --> 00:53:10,200
My mom asked me when I'm coming, too.

610
00:53:11,620 --> 00:53:13,530
Thank you.

611
00:53:14,170 --> 00:53:15,600
Bye!

612
00:53:21,940 --> 00:53:24,800
Where should we go now?

613
00:53:24,800 --> 00:53:26,400
Should we just go home?

614
00:53:26,400 --> 00:53:29,810
I still haven't digested that steak.

615
00:53:29,810 --> 00:53:31,470
How do you feel?

616
00:53:31,470 --> 00:53:33,110
I feel fine.

617
00:53:33,110 --> 00:53:34,540
Auntie.

618
00:53:35,230 --> 00:53:37,180
You're here.

619
00:53:38,110 --> 00:53:40,160
He must be your nephew.

620
00:53:40,160 --> 00:53:42,010
Yes.

621
00:53:43,110 --> 00:53:44,830
Do you feel okay?

622
00:53:44,830 --> 00:53:46,990
Did you see the baby?

623
00:53:46,990 --> 00:53:49,610
She looks the same as her photo. She's so cute.

624
00:53:49,610 --> 00:53:51,900
Your nephew must take after his maternal side.

625
00:53:51,900 --> 00:53:55,430
He looks exactly like his mom and aunt.

626
00:53:55,430 --> 00:53:56,530
What's the "maternal side"?

627
00:53:56,530 --> 00:54:00,150
I'm saying you resemble your mom's family more than your dad's.

628
00:54:00,150 --> 00:54:01,400
"Mom's family"?

629
00:54:01,400 --> 00:54:04,040
What are you saying? He doesn't.

630
00:54:04,040 --> 00:54:06,820
Wasn't the woman from a few days ago your older sister?

631
00:54:06,820 --> 00:54:11,060
They look so similar. I could tell he was her son right away.

632
00:54:31,890 --> 00:54:33,650
Mom was here?

633
00:54:33,650 --> 00:54:35,800
Who was here?

634
00:54:35,800 --> 00:54:37,700
Hae Joon's mom.

635
00:54:37,700 --> 00:54:42,200
She came and left without seeing Hae Joon? Why?

636
00:54:42,200 --> 00:54:44,280
Who knows?

637
00:54:45,370 --> 00:54:49,680
Depositing this in the bank would feel like I'm getting rid of evidence,

638
00:54:49,680 --> 00:54:52,960
but I can't exactly hide this large sum anywhere.

639
00:54:52,960 --> 00:54:55,820
Gosh, I really don't know what to do.

640
00:54:55,820 --> 00:54:57,550
What do you think?

641
00:54:57,550 --> 00:55:00,100
You can use it for Hae Joon's college next year.

642
00:55:00,100 --> 00:55:02,170
Don't say a word about it to Hae Joon.

643
00:55:02,170 --> 00:55:05,040
She might have some circumstances.

644
00:55:05,040 --> 00:55:08,600
What dire circumstance would stop her from seeing her child's face?

645
00:55:08,600 --> 00:55:12,050
You don't have to feel guilty; this was your money to start with.

646
00:55:12,050 --> 00:55:14,730
What's the problem with getting your money back?

647
00:55:17,590 --> 00:55:19,420
Even so.

648
00:55:19,420 --> 00:55:21,260
"Your mom paid her debt and left."

649
00:55:21,260 --> 00:55:23,000
"She left without seeing you."

650
00:55:23,000 --> 00:55:24,950
Can you tell him that?

651
00:55:30,150 --> 00:55:34,180
 She said she paid her debt before leaving. 

652
00:55:35,540 --> 00:55:42,220
 So she said not to worry about the money. 

653
00:56:06,570 --> 00:56:10,440
I can repay the money later when I'm older.

654
00:56:14,140 --> 00:56:16,800
I could have repaid it.

655
00:56:34,080 --> 00:56:36,390
Did you give Dal your notes?

656
00:56:36,390 --> 00:56:39,130
What do you think? Did she seem better?

657
00:56:39,130 --> 00:56:40,620
Yes.

658
00:56:41,810 --> 00:56:44,730
Anyway, why is Kang Hae Joon so dense?

659
00:56:44,730 --> 00:56:47,560
You're the one Dal's mom wanted to see.

660
00:56:47,560 --> 00:56:50,470
Why does he think I brought him along if he's not involved?

661
00:56:50,470 --> 00:56:53,700
Wasn't that enough for most people to catch on?

662
00:56:55,350 --> 00:56:56,550
Right?

663
00:56:56,550 --> 00:56:57,950
Pardon?

664
00:56:59,040 --> 00:57:00,700
You weren't listening.

665
00:57:00,700 --> 00:57:02,000
I was.

666
00:57:02,000 --> 00:57:04,350
What did I say?

667
00:57:04,350 --> 00:57:07,350
That Kang Hae Joon is dense.

668
00:57:08,490 --> 00:57:10,570
Do you know what he said to me earlier?

669
00:57:10,570 --> 00:57:14,230
He said he's positive Dal has feelings for Kim San Ha.

670
00:57:14,230 --> 00:57:16,280
He said he's astute.

671
00:57:17,910 --> 00:57:19,520
Yeah, right.

672
00:57:22,170 --> 00:57:24,480
What are you doing? You'll fall.

673
00:57:24,480 --> 00:57:27,050
Wow, this feels nice.

674
00:57:28,300 --> 00:57:29,890
Come up.

675
00:57:31,260 --> 00:57:34,430
Grab on. It's dangerous.

676
00:57:34,430 --> 00:57:36,360
Am I a child?

677
00:57:42,220 --> 00:57:47,740
Doesn't he think about why Dal and I go to his basketball practice?

678
00:57:47,740 --> 00:57:50,030
I don't even know basketball rules.

679
00:57:50,030 --> 00:57:52,460
I'm just following Dal.

680
00:57:53,160 --> 00:57:54,760
Exactly.

681
00:57:55,860 --> 00:57:59,160
She always stops by the gym on her way to the academy.

682
00:57:59,160 --> 00:58:02,150
Isn't that quite a blatant signal?

683
00:58:02,150 --> 00:58:04,340
Was he always so dense?

684
00:58:04,340 --> 00:58:06,030
Don't you agree?

685
00:58:09,630 --> 00:58:11,280
You're dense, too.

686
00:58:11,280 --> 00:58:13,530
Why am I–

687
00:58:20,070 --> 00:58:30,010


688
00:58:32,500 --> 00:58:36,350
♫  I keep rattling  ♫

689
00:58:38,410 --> 00:58:43,240
♫  Like a broken doll  ♫

690
00:58:44,340 --> 00:58:48,830
♫  I'm lost on every step  ♫

691
00:58:50,260 --> 00:58:55,140
♫  I guess I'm locked away inside you  ♫

692
00:58:56,010 --> 00:58:59,000
♫  I need an explanation  ♫

693
00:58:59,000 --> 00:59:05,860
♫  My day is spent immersed in a dream  ♫

694
00:59:07,850 --> 00:59:11,520
♫  I have a lot to say  ♫

695
00:59:12,330 --> 00:59:18,600
♫  but I'm lost for words  ♫

696
00:59:24,780 --> 00:59:30,700
♫  Why am I like this?  ♫

697
00:59:30,700 --> 00:59:38,730
♫  Why am I always so excited like it's the first time?  ♫

698
00:59:38,730 --> 00:59:44,480
♫  And remorseful like it's the last time?  ♫

699
00:59:44,480 --> 00:59:48,330
♫  Again, I circle around you like I'm praying  ♫

700
00:59:48,330 --> 00:59:54,190
♫  When our eyes meet  ♫

701
00:59:54,190 --> 00:59:55,900
   

702
00:59:55,900 --> 00:59:58,390
 Doesn't Kim San Ha seem sensitive these days? 

703
00:59:58,390 --> 01:00:01,180
 The CSAT is next week. I need to focus. 

704
01:00:01,180 --> 01:00:03,150
 She should be more careful. 

705
01:00:03,150 --> 01:00:05,280
 Boldly skip the questions you don't know. 

706
01:00:05,280 --> 01:00:07,550
 If worst comes to worst, roll your pencil! 

707
01:00:07,550 --> 01:00:10,870
 Congrats on finishing the CSAT! 

708
01:00:11,570 --> 01:00:14,860
 If she left, she should've lived a good life. Why make him suffer? 

709
01:00:14,860 --> 01:00:16,610
 Let go! 

710
01:00:16,610 --> 01:00:18,820
 It's only been one day since you went to Seoul. 

711
01:00:18,820 --> 01:00:21,770
 - Why does it seem so long ago? 
 - Oppa! 

712
01:00:21,770 --> 01:00:24,410
 The time it takes to wake up from anesthesia varies for everyone, 

713
01:00:24,410 --> 01:00:31,350
 but something feels off. 

714
01:00:31,350 --> 01:00:33,520
♫  These days...  ♫

